main event: An oval-shaped, white fluorescent object was observed for 25 minutes over Randolph AFB, Texas on October 4, 1959.
interesting points: The object appeared to remain almost stationary and move slowly in a southerly direction, with no discernible features or details.
The observers were in a moving automobile, and the object appeared to remain in the immediate area two miles south of Randolph AFB.
The investigating officer believed the observer to be above-average in qualifications regarding this type of incident, and the observer was described as stable, intelligent, and coherent.

Preliminary analysis indicated no probable cause for the sighting, and there were no reports of the object from Randolph Tower, GCA, Brooks AFB Tower, ACW GCI at Lackland AFB, or San Antonio Center Radar.
The weather conditions at the time included clear skies in the immediate area, with thunderstorms and lightning to the north, and moderate wind speeds.
witnesses: Civilian observers in a moving automobile
